  "name": "Cleansing Flame",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/spells/explosion-orange-2.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 9th level, twice per day, you can use fire to restore the health of yourself or your allies. As a standard action, you can wreathe your hand in a halo of flame and touch yourself or another creature. The touch heals 2d8 + your character level points of damage. You can also remove one of the following conditions affecting the target: 1d6 points of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores/#Ability_Score_Damage\">ability damage</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Blinded\">blinded</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Confused\">confused</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Dazzled\">dazzled</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Deafened\">deafened</a>, diseased,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Exhausted\">exhausted</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Fatigued\">fatigued</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Nauseated\">nauseated</a>, poisoned, or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions/#TOC-Sickened\">sickened</a>. At 20th level, you can use this ability three times per day.</p>"
    },
